        "type": "text_delta",
        "content": "I tested the toolset in a throwaway temp directory: `/tmp/tmp.m4yJpzPolc`.\n\nWhat I exercised\n- Filesystem:\n  - `glob`\n  - `grep`\n  - `read_file`\n- Editing:\n  - `apply_patch`\n- Commands:\n  - `exec_command`\n  - `write_stdin`\n- Coordination:\n  - `update_plan`\n  - `agent_call`\n  - `agent_result`\n  - `ask`\n  - `batch`\n  - `multi_tool_use.parallel`\n- Web:\n  - `search_web`\n  - `fetch_url`\n\nWhat worked well\n- Temp workspace creation succeeded.\n- File creation, discovery, content search, and file reads all worked.\n- Patch application worked; I created `patched.txt` and verified its contents.\n- One-shot shell commands worked.\n- Interactive PTY flow worked:\n  - started `cat`\n  - sent input with `write_stdin`\n  - got echoed output\n  - closed stdin cleanly\n- Delegation worked:\n  - spawned a child agent\n  - it inspected the temp dir\n  - returned a structured result\n- Parallel wrappers worked:\n  - `batch` successfully ran multiple independent calls\n  - `multi_tool_use.parallel` also succeeded\n- Web tools worked:\n  - web search returned successfully\n  - URL fetch from `https://example.com/` returned successfully\n\nMinor caveats\n- The `ask` tool necessarily pauses for an answer"
      }
    },
    {
      "op": "event",
      "event": {
        "type": "text_delta",
        "content": "; for this self-test I used it in a harmless way and proceeded.\n- `batch` reports success compactly; if you need the detailed payload from each call, separate direct calls can be easier to inspect.\n- I did not test `agent_kill` because it’s a cancellation path rather than a normal success path, and there was no need to interrupt a running child.\n\nBottom line\n- Yes: the tools work well overall.\n- The local file, shell, edit, orchestration, delegation, and web flows all behaved as expected in this test.\n\nIf you want, I can do a second pass that specifically stress-tests edge cases like failures, timeouts, and cancellation behavior."
      }
